Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel first
if you prefer). Cut into 1cm chunks and pop onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then sprinkle over the @ground
cumin{1%tsp}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and cooked through,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @radishes{100}.

Cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} into small pieces.

== Harissa Yoghurt ==

In a large #bowl{}, mix together the @low fat natural yoghurt{150%g} and
@harissa paste{50%g} (use less if you'd prefer things milder).

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then set aside.

== Warm Naans ==

When the butternut has ~{5%minutes} left, remove from the oven and sprinkle with
the @flaked almonds{15%g}. Return to the oven for the remaining time.

Meanwhile, put the @plain naans{2} onto a baking tray. Sprinkle with a little
@water{} and pop them into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, add the @wild rocket{20%g}, radishes and tomato to the harissa dressing.
Toss to coat.

When everything is ready, lay a naan on each #plate{}.

Top with the roasted butternut and harissa-dressed salad.

Scatter over the flaked almonds, Greek style salad cheese, and @dukkah mix{1%tsp}
to finish. Enjoy!